{
  "text": "Would you define mind, body, and spirit separately? I and Ra. These terms are all simplistic descriptive terms which equal a complex of energy, of focuses, the body, as you call it, being the material of the density which you experience at a given space-time or a time space, this complex of materials being available for distortions of what you would call a physical manifestation. The mind is a complex which reflects the in pourings of the spirit and the up pourings of the body complex. It contains what you know as feelings, emotions, and intellectual thoughts in its more conscious complexities, a moving further down the tree of a mind, we see the intuition which is of the nature of the mind more in a contact or in a tune with the total beingness complex, moving down to the roots of a mind, we find the progression of a consciousness which gradually turns from the personal to the racial memory, to the cosmic influxes, and thus becomes a direct contactor of that, a shuttle which we call the spirit complex. This spirit complex is the channel whereby the in pourings from all of the Avarius, a universal, a planetary, and a personal inpourings may be funneled into the roots of consciousness and whereby consciousness may be a funnel to the gateway of intelligent infinity through the balanced intelligent energy of a body and a mind you will see by this series of definitive statements that mind, a body, and spirit are inextricably intertwined and cannot continue one without the other. Thus we refer to the mind, body, spirit, complex rather than attempting to deal with them separately for the work, shall we say that you do during your experiences is done through the interaction of these three components, not through any one.",
  "timestamps": {
    "segment": [
      {
        "segment": "Would you define mind, body, and spirit separately?",
        "start_offset": 69,
